# Repository-wide line-ending discipline.
#
# Markdown is checked in with LF endings on every platform so System
# Facts / checklists / briefs are diff-stable across the operator's
# machines, CI checkouts, and the remote Claude execution environment.
# Without this, an editor on a Windows checkout could rewrite every
# .md file to CRLF on first save and produce a 600-line phantom diff.
#
# No pre-existing .editorconfig or .gitattributes to reconcile with
# (verified 2026-05-31 on `claude/bold-meitner-l1VGm`); this is the
# first declaration of EOL policy in the repo. If an .editorconfig
# is added later, mirror `end_of_line = lf` for `*.md` there too —
# Git's policy here normalizes the working tree; .editorconfig
# normalizes the editor.

*.md text eol=lf
